Creating a 2D game with important teachings about Buddhism that's fully functional requires a significant amount of code and design work. Below is a simplified HTML file that simulates a text-based game incorporating some Buddhist teachings with non-playable characters (NPCs) and a basic interactive interface. This is not a full-fledged game, but it illustrates fundamental concepts such as compassion, mindfulness, and impermanence.

You can copy and paste the following code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser to play the game.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Buddhist Teachings Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background: #f0f8ff;
            color: #333;
        }
        #game {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            margin: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            border-radius: 10px;
            background: #fff;
        }
        #npc-dialogue, #user-action {
            margin: 15px 0;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="game">
        <h1>Buddhist Teachings Adventure</h1>
        <div id="npc-dialogue"></div>
        <div id="user-action"></div>
        <button id="option1" onclick="makeChoice(1)">Option 1</button>
        <button id="option2" onclick="makeChoice(2)">Option 2</button>
        <button id="option3" onclick="makeChoice(3)">Option 3</button>
    </div>

    <script>
        const dialogues = [
            {
                text: "Welcome, traveler! I am the monk. Would you like to learn about compassion or mindfulness?",
                options: [
                    { text: "Learn about Compassion", nextDialogueIndex: 1 },
                    { text: "Learn about Mindfulness", nextDialogueIndex: 2 },
                ]
            },
            {
                text: "Compassion is the wish for all beings to be free from suffering. Practice it daily.",
                options: [
                    { text: "Move on", nextDialogueIndex: 0 }
                ]
            },
            {
                text: "Mindfulness means being present in the moment. Notice your thoughts and feelings without judgment.",
                options: [
                    { text: "Move on", nextDialogueIndex: 0 }
                ]
            },
        ];

        let currentDialogueIndex = 0;

        function displayDialogue() {
            const dialogue = dialogues[currentDialogueIndex];
            document.getElementById('npc-dialogue').innerText = dialogue.text;
            const actions = dialogue.options.map((option, index) => {
                document.getElementById(`option${index + 1}`).innerText = option.text;
                return option;
            });

            for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
                if (i >= actions.length) {
                    document.getElementById(`option${i + 1}`).style.display = "none";
                } else {
                    document.getElementById(`option${i + 1}`).style.display = "inline";
                }
            }
        }

        function makeChoice(optionIndex) {
            const selectedOption = dialogues[currentDialogueIndex].options[optionIndex - 1];
            currentDialogueIndex = selectedOption.nextDialogueIndex;
            displayDialogue();
        }

        // Initialize the game
        displayDialogue();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use the Code:
1. Copy the entire code provided above.
2. Paste it into a text editor (like Notepad, Visual Studio Code, etc.).
3. Save the file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `buddhist_game.html`).
4. Open the saved file in a web browser to start playing the game.

### Features of the Game:
- There are basic interactions with NPCs (non-playable characters).
- Players can choose to learn about two fundamental teachings: compassion and mindfulness.
- The game is designed in a simple text-based format to teach players about Buddhist concepts without complex graphics or mechanics.

Feel free to expand upon this foundation to include more teachings, NPC interactions, and different story paths!
